                "text_rotate": ""
            }
        },
        {
            "category_type": "plain_text",
            "poly": [
                1250,
                802.5,
                2302.5,
                802.5,
                2302.5,
                1287.5,
                1250,
                1287.5
            ],
            "ignore": false,
            "order": 12,
            "anno_id": 1,
            "text": " To construct autonomous robots that can be used in agricultural environments for a variety of tasks, such as harvest management (crops, vegetables, or fruits), field farming, crop management, higher levels of sophistication in perception, complex planning capacity, effective control mechanisms, and increased learning capability, are needed to adapt new environments with daunting challenges for the future. As a result, a thorough understanding of autonomous systems, their behavior, and the overall architecture of the system must be realized, and this remains an important research subject.",
